  "text": ", n)wt(f ) operations, which is close to 2 3n−3 when f is balanced. As noted in [CITATION_1] , the complexity can be significantly reduced if we only want to check whether a function has annihilators of small degree d, since we do not need to consider all positions in the support of f . Indeed, considering a number of columns which is only slightly higher that the code dimension k(d, n) is usually sufficient for proving that a function does not admit any annihilator of degree d.",
